                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ambassador Reid telegraphs substance of a conversation he has had with British
                    minister for foreign affairs in which he indicated the disposition of the
                    British Government to make some informal representations regarding Kongo affairs
                    and intimated that British minister to Belgium might concert with you on the
                    subject.</p>
                <p>You will be instructed later—probably Monday—as to your course, and if in the
                    meantime the British minister should approach you you will advise the department
                    of such suggestions as he may make.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
